                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d376">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/5–1050: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>, at London</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-05-10T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 10, 1950—4 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Tosec1">Tosec</gloss> 157. Personal to the Secretary from
                        Dulles.<note n="1" xml:id="d376fn1">John Foster Dulles, Consultant to the
                        Secretary of State.</note> I have just read the text of Schuman’s statement
                    regarding new political authority to unify and administer German-French coal and
                    steel resources. While obviously many details lacking necessary for final
                    judgment, it is my initial impression that the conception is brilliantly
                    creative and could go far to solve the most dangerous problem of our time,
                    namely the relationship of Germany’s industrial power to France and the West.
                    This proposal is along lines which Secretary Marshall and I thought <pb
                        facs="0720" n="696" xml:id="pg_696"/> about in Moscow in 1947 but which we
                    did not believe the French would ever accept. [Dulles.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
